    ),
    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Common-Control Accounting Treatment & Recast Financials Disclosure\n\n## Overview of the Mergers\n\nIn 2025, **xAI completed its acquisition of X Holdings Corp. ("X") and X.AI Corp.**, making them wholly-owned subsidiaries of xAI (the "X Merger"). Subsequently, on **February 2, 2026**, **SpaceX completed its acquisition of xAI** (the "xAI Merger"). Collectively, these are referred to as the "Mergers." Each merger was effected through a share exchange.\n\nKey timeline:\n- **October 2022** — Elon Musk acquired Twitter, Inc. (renamed to X Holdings)\n- **March 2023** — X.AI Corp. began operations\n- **March 28, 2025** — xAI acquired X Holdings and X.AI Corp. (X Merger)\n- **February 2, 2026** — SpaceX acquired xAI (xAI Merger)\n\n---\n\n## Why Common-Control Accounting Applies\n\nThe Mergers were **accounted for as reorganizations of entities under common control** because **Elon Musk had a controlling financial interest** in SpaceX, xAI, and X through his **majority voting interest** in each entity during all periods presented in the consolidated financial statements.\n\nBecause all three entities were under the same ultimate controlling party, U.S. GAAP requires these transactions to be treated not as acquisitions at fair value, but as **combinations of entities under common control** — essentially reorganizing what was already a single economic enterprise.\n\n---\n\n## Retrospective Combination — The Core Treatment\n\nThe Company\'s consolidated financial statements were prepared to reflect:\n\n1. **Retrospective combination of net assets** at their **historical carrying amounts** for **all periods presented** — meaning the financials of xAI and X are woven into SpaceX\'s historical statements as if the combined entity had always existed in this form.\n\n2. **No new goodwill or other intangible assets** were recorded — because under common-control accounting, assets are carried at historical book values, not fair value.\n\n3. **All historical related-party transactions** between the entities (SpaceX, xAI, and X) **have been eliminated in consolidation** — ensuring no double-counting of intercompany revenue, expenses, receivables, or payables.\n\n> *"The consolidated financial statements of SpaceX have been retrospectively recast for all periods presented to include (i) the historical results of X.AI Holdings Corp., which was acquired by SpaceX, effective February 2, 2026 (the \'xAI Merger\'), and X Holdings Corp. (\'X Holdings\'), which was acquired by xAI, effective March 28, 2025 (the \'X Merger\'), because these transactions were between entities under common control."*\n\n---\n\n## Capital Stock & Equity Treatment\n\nThe **capital stock and shareholders\' equity** for all periods presented reflects:\n\n- A **continuation of the historical SpaceX capital stock and shareholders\' equity**\n- **Combined with** the historical capital stock and shareholders\' equity of X and xAI\n- **Adjusted by the respective exchange ratios** used to effect the Mergers\n- **Except** for xAI\'s historical redeemable convertible preferred stock (treated differently — see below)\n\n### Exchange Ratios\n\n| Conversion | Ratio |\n|---|---|\n| **xAI Common Stock → SpaceX Common Stock** | 0.1433 SpaceX shares per xAI share (pre-2026 Stock Split) |\n| **X Holdings Common Stock → xAI Common Stock** | 2.776 xAI shares per X share (same class) |\n| **X.AI Corp. Common Stock → xAI Common Stock** | 1.000:1 (same class) |\n| **xAI warrants → SpaceX Class A Common Stock** | 0.1433 (cashless exercise triggered by merger) |\n\nAs a result, all historical shares of X, X.AI Corp., and xAI Common Stock are **presented as if converted into SpaceX Common Stock** at the applicable exchange rate for all periods presented. All share and per-share information is retroactively adjusted.\n\nA **cash election option** existed for eligible service providers:\n- $75.46 per share of xAI Class A or Class B Common Stock\n- Cash option for xAI Series A Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock\n\n---\n\n## Special Treatment of xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock\n\nThis is a critical nuance. Although xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock **converted into SpaceX Common Stock** upon closing of the xAI Merger:\n\n- The balances are **presented as Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock** in the consolidated financial statements **for all periods presented prior to the xAI Merger Date**\n- This is because the preferred stock was **legally outstanding during all historical periods** and represented **a separate equity class of a legally distinct predecessor entity**\n- The conversion is **recognized only in the period in which the exchange actually occurs** (Q1 2026), and **not retrospectively**\n- Historical consolidated balance sheets reflect xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock **consistent with its legal form and rights** during those periods — **not on an as-converted basis**\n\n> *"Because the xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was legally outstanding during all historical periods prior to the xAI Merger and represented a separate equity class of a legally distinct predecessor entity, the conversion of xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock into SpaceX Common Stock is recognized only in the period in which the exchange actually occurs, and not retrospectively."*\n\nThe impact of the conversion is presented **prospectively in the consolidated statements of redeemable convertible preferred stock and shareholders\' equity** for the three months ended March 31, 2026.\n\nThe accounting entry for the conversion (as shown in the Q1 2026 statement of equity):\n- **Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock decreased by ~$37,476 million** (1,987 shares)\n- **Common Stock increased by 1,424 shares**\n- **Additional Paid-in Capital increased by ~$37,474 million**\n\n---\n\n## Change in Reporting Entity\n\nThis presentation **constitutes a change in reporting entity** under U.S. GAAP. As the consolidated financial statements already reflect the reorganization of entities under common control for all periods presented, **separate financial statements of xAI and X are not provided**.\n\n---\n\n## Additional Adjustment: 2026 Stock Split\n\nOn **May 4, 2026**, SpaceX effected a **five-for-one forward stock split** of its authorized, issued, and outstanding shares of Class A, Class B, and Class C Common Stock. The conversion rate of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was proportionately adjusted. **All share and per-share information has been retroactively adjusted** to reflect this split for all periods presented.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Accounting Principles\n\n| Principle | Treatment |\n|---|---|\n| **Combination basis** | Retrospective, at historical carrying amounts |\n| **Goodwill/intangibles** | None recorded |\n| **Intercompany transactions** | Fully eliminated in consolidation |\n| **Common stock shares** | Retroactively restated at exchange ratios |\n| **xAI Redeemable Preferred** | Presented historically at carrying value; conversion recognized prospectively in Q1 2026 |\n| **Stock split** | Retroactively applied to all periods |\n| **Reporting entity change** | Yes — disclosure required |\n| **Separate financials** | Not provided (already reflected in consolidation) |\n| **GAAP compliance** | U.S. GAAP, with management estimates |',
        error=None,
        metadata=None,
        done=False,
