lude (i) the historical results of X.AI Holdings Corp... and X Holdings Corp... because these transactions were between entities under common control."\n*   **Change in Reporting Entity:** This process is defined as a "**change in reporting entity**." Historical financial data is not the data of the original SpaceX alone, but a combined presentation. Key details include:\n    *   Assets are presented at **historical carrying amounts**, not fair value.\n    *   All **historical related party transactions** between the entities have been eliminated.\n    *   Capital stock and equity reflect a continuation and combination of each entity\'s historical capital structure.\n    *   **Exception for Redeemable Preferred Stock:** The conversion of xAI\'s redeemable convertible preferred stock into SpaceX common stock is recognized **only prospectively** (upon the merger date in Q1 2026), not retrospectively. This creates a discontinuity in how equity instruments are presented across periods.\n\n### 4. Summary of Cautionary Language\nThe prospectus consistently warns readers about the limitations of the provided historical data in the context of these profound structural changes. It directs them to the **Risk Factors** section (referenced but not fully included in your excerpts) for a discussion of specific factors that could cause future results to differ.\n\n**In essence, the disclosures state that due to the major restructuring via common-control mergers, the historical financials are a **recast combination** of previously separate entities, not the results of a stable, standalone company. Investors are explicitly cautioned against using these historical figures to predict future performance.**',
